<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>AI4HSE — AI-Native HSE Intelligence Layer</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #05040d;
      --bg-alt: #0b0618;
      --bg-soft: #120b26;
      --accent: #8b5cff;
      --accent2: #c084fc;
      --success: #3dd68c;
      --text: #f7f4ff;
      --muted: #a8a2c0;
      --border: #241b3f;
      --radius: 14px;
      --max-width: 1120px;
    }

    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #1a1038 0, #05040d 60%);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }

    /* Layout */
    .page { min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    section { padding: 70px 20px; }
    .inner { max-width: var(--max-width); margin: 0 auto; }

    /* Header */
    header {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 20;
      backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(5,4,13,0.96), rgba(5,4,13,0.75));
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    }
    .nav {
      max-width: var(--max-width);
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 14px 20px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 24px;
    }
    .logo {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .logo-mark {
      width: 28px;
      height: 28px;
      border-radius: 9px;
      background: conic-gradient(from 210deg, #8b5cff, #c084fc, #7dd3ff, #8b5cff);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #fff;
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      font-size: 15px;
    }
    .nav-links {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 22px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .nav-links a {
      position: relative;
      padding: 4px 0;
    }
    .nav-links a::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      bottom: -4px;
      width: 0;
      height: 2px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent), var(--accent2));
      transition: width 0.18s ease-out;
    }
    .nav-links a:hover::after { width: 100%; }

    .nav-cta {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .btn {
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 8px 18px;
      font-size: 14px;
      border: 1px solid transparent;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: all 0.18s ease-out;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--text);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .btn-outline {
      border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.18);
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .btn-outline:hover {
      border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
      color: var(--text);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    }
    .btn-primary {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), var(--accent2));
      box-shadow: 0 10px 26px rgba(139,92,255,0.55);
      border: none;
    }
    .btn-primary:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
      box-shadow: 0 14px 34px rgba(139,92,255,0.7);
    }

    /* Hero */
    .hero {
      padding-top: 80px;
      padding-bottom: 70px;
    }
    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.4fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
      gap: 40px;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      padding: 4px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(139,92,255,0.12);
      border: 1px solid rgba(192,132,252,0.5);
      color: #e9ddff;
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
    .eyebrow-dot {
      width: 7px;
      height: 7px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: var(--success);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(61,214,140,0.25);
    }
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 40px;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .hero-title span {
      background: linear-gradient(120deg, #8b5cff, #c084fc, #7dd3ff);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      color: transparent;
    }
    .hero-sub {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 15px;
      max-width: 540px;
      margin-bottom: 22px;
    }
    .hero-actions {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 12px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .hero-note {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .hero-card {
      border-radius: 20px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, #261a4b 0, #0b0618 55%);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      padding: 20px 18px 18px;
      box-shadow: 0 18px 45px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .hero-card::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: -40%;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 10% 0, rgba(192,132,252,0.22), transparent 55%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 90% 100%, rgba(139,92,255,0.2), transparent 55%);
      opacity: 0.9;
      mix-blend-mode: screen;
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .hero-card-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
    .hero-card-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .hero-card-sub {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .hero-stats {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 18px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .stat {
      min-width: 110px;
    }
    .stat-value {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .stat-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      margin-top: 2px;
    }
    .hero-card-footer {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      padding-top: 10px;
      margin-top: 4px;
    }

    /* Section headings */
    .section-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-size: 26px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .section-lead {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--muted);
      max-width: 640px;
    }

    /* Why / Problem */
    .two-col {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
      gap: 26px;
      margin-top: 26px;
    }
    .card {
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 18px 18px 16px;
      background: var(--bg-alt);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .card-header {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .card-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .card-tag {
      font-size: 11px;
      padding: 3px 8px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .card-body {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .card-list {
      margin-top: 10px;
      list-style: none;
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .card-list li {
      display: flex;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .bullet {
      width: 5px;
      height: 5px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      margin-top: 7px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    }
    .bullet-accent { background: var(--accent2); }

    /* Feature grid */
    .feature-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 18px;
      margin-top: 24px;
    }
    .feature {
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 16px 14px 14px;
      background: var(--bg-alt);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .feature-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .feature-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .feature-body {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    /* Industries pills */
    .pill-row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-top: 18px;
    }
    .pill {
      font-size: 11px;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(18,11,38,0.9);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    /* Quote */
    .quote {
      border-radius: 20px;
      padding: 20px 20px 18px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(139,92,255,0.22), #05040d 55%);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
      margin-top: 26px;
      box-shadow: 0 18px 45px rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
    }
    .quote-text {
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .quote-meta {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    /* CTA + contact */
    .cta-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
      gap: 26px;
      margin-top: 26px;
    }
    .cta-card {
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 20px 18px 18px;
      background: var(--bg-alt);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .cta-title {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .cta-body {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    form {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 12px 14px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }
    .field {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 4px;
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .field label {
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .field input,
    .field textarea {
      border-radius: 10px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: rgba(11,6,24,0.95);
      padding: 8px 10px;
      color: var(--text);
      font-size: 13px;
      outline: none;
      transition: border-color 0.16s ease-out, box-shadow 0.16s ease-out;
    }
    .field input:focus,
    .field textarea:focus {
      border-color: var(--accent);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(139,92,255,0.5);
    }
    .field textarea {
      min-height: 80px;
      resize: vertical;
    }
    .field-full { grid-column: 1 / -1; }

    .form-footer {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 4px;
      font-size: 11px;
      color: var(--muted);
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    footer {
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      padding: 18px 20px 26px;
      background: #05040d;
    }
    .footer-inner {
      max-width: var(--max-width);
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 12px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .footer-links {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 14px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .hero-grid,
      .two-col,
      .feature-grid,
      .cta-grid {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      }
      .hero {
        padding-top: 60px;
      }
      .hero-title {
        font-size: 32px;
      }
      .nav-links {
        display: none;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .feature-grid {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      }
      form {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      }
      .hero-card {
        margin-top: 10px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <header>
    <div class="nav">
      <div class="logo">
        <div class="logo-mark">A4</div>
        <span>AI4HSE</span>
      </div>
      <nav class="nav-links">
        <a href="#why">Why AI4HSE</a>
        <a href="#platform">Intelligence Layer</a>
        <a href="#modules">Modules</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="nav-cta">
        <button class="btn-outline" onclick="scrollToId('contact')">Contact</button>
        <button class="btn-primary" onclick="scrollToId('contact')">Request Demo →</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="inner hero-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">
            <span class="eyebrow-dot"></span>
            AI-Native HSE Intelligence Layer
          </div>
          <h1 class="hero-title">
            Real-time intelligence for<br />
            <span>HSE, risk & ESG at scale</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">
            AI4HSE sits above your operations as an intelligence layer — unifying HSE, risk, ESG,
            compliance, and field data into one live view of operational reality. Built for Oil & Gas,
            Utilities, Mining, Manufacturing, Aviation, and giga‑projects across the Middle East.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <button class="btn-primary" onclick="scrollToId('contact')">
              Request a Live Demo →
            </button>
            <button class="btn-outline" onclick="scrollToId('platform')">
              Explore the Intelligence Layer
            </button>
          </div>
          <p class="hero-note">
            Designed from 14+ years of real-world HSE transformation — not from a slide deck.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-card">
          <div class="hero-card-inner">
            <div class="hero-card-title">Live Operational Risk Posture</div>
            <div class="hero-card-sub">
              AI4HSE continuously ingests incidents, inspections, permits, and ESG data to surface
              where your next serious event is most likely to occur.
            </div>

            <div class="hero-stats">
              <div class="stat">
                <div class="stat-value">92%</div>
                <div class="stat-label">Critical controls healthy</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat">
                <div class="stat-value">↓ 37%</div>
                <div class="stat-label">Incidents YoY</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat">
                <div class="stat-value">98.4%</div>
                <div class="stat-label">Compliance on-time</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="hero-card-footer">
              Every insight is traceable back to source data — no black-box AI, no manual reconciliation.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why -->
    <section id="why">
      <div class="inner">
        <div class="section-label">Why AI4HSE</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Legacy HSE systems weren’t built as intelligence layers.</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
          Most HSE and GRC platforms grew through acquisitions — multiple products stitched together with APIs,
          inconsistent workflows, and fragmented data. They record events, but they don’t truly understand them.
          AI4HSE is different: it’s an AI-native intelligence layer designed to interpret, connect, and predict.
        </p>

        <div class="pill-row">
          <span class="pill">Oil & Gas</span>
          <span class="pill">Utilities</span>
          <span class="pill">Mining</span>
          <span class="pill">Manufacturing</span>
          <span class="pill">Aviation</span>
          <span class="pill">Giga‑projects</span>
        </div>

        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <div class="card-title">The fragmented HSE stack</div>
              <span class="card-tag">Yesterday’s reality</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              Separate tools for incidents, audits, risk, ESG, and permits — each with its own data model,
              workflows, and reports. You spend more time reconciling than improving safety.
            </div>
            <ul class="card-list">
              <li>
                <span class="bullet"></span>
                <span>Multiple vendors, overlapping modules, and duplicated data.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="bullet"></span>
                <span>APIs and spreadsheets holding everything together.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="bullet"></span>
                <span>Lagging indicators, static dashboards, and manual analysis.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="bullet"></span>
                <span>Upgrades and changes are slow, risky, and expensive.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <div class="card-title">AI4HSE: the intelligence layer</div>
              <span class="card-tag">Designed for now</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              AI4HSE doesn’t replace every system on day one — it connects, interprets, and elevates them.
              It becomes the live, AI-native brain for your HSE, risk, and ESG ecosystem.
            </div>
            <ul class="card-list">
              <li>
                <span class="bullet bullet-accent"></span>
                <span>Unifies incidents, inspections, PTW, risk, and ESG into one model.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="bullet bullet-accent"></span>
                <span>Surfaces leading indicators and emerging patterns in real time.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="bullet bullet-accent"></span>
                <span>Embeds AI into workflows — not as a chatbot bolted on the side.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="bullet bullet-accent"></span>
                <span>Built for Middle East scale, regulation, and complexity.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Platform / Intelligence Layer -->
    <section id="platform">
      <div class="inner">
        <div class="section-label">Intelligence layer</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">One AI-native layer across HSE, risk, ESG & compliance.</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
          AI4HSE ingests data from your existing systems — incident management, PTW, ERP, ESG tools — and
          transforms it into a single, coherent intelligence layer. Every module shares the same data model,
          AI engine, and security framework.
        </p>

        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Risk</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Unified risk intelligence</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Bowtie, JSA/JHA, enterprise risk, and environmental aspects/impacts connected to real incidents,
              controls, and actions — not just static registers.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Signals</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Leading indicator engine</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              AI models detect weak signals across near misses, unsafe acts, overdue actions, and permit data
              to highlight where serious events are most likely to emerge.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Context</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Operational context graph</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Assets, locations, contractors, activities, and people linked into a graph — so AI4HSE understands
              not just what happened, but where, how, and to whom.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">AI</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Explainable AI insights</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Every recommendation is backed by traceable evidence — source events, controls, and trends —
              giving HSE leaders confidence to act.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Security</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Enterprise-grade controls</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              SSO, role-based access, data residency options, and audit trails designed for regulated,
              safety-critical environments.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Middle East</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Built for regional realities</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Supports Arabic/English, regional regulations, and giga‑project scale — aligned with the
              transformation agendas of GCC governments and national champions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="quote">
          <p class="quote-text">
            “AI4HSE is the intelligence layer we wished existed while implementing HSE and GRC platforms
            across Oil & Gas, Utilities, Mining, and giga‑projects. It doesn’t just digitize forms —
            it understands risk, context, and consequence.”
          </p>
          <div class="quote-meta">
            Founder, AI4HSE — Built from 14+ years of real-world implementations.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Modules -->
    <section id="modules">
      <div class="inner">
        <div class="section-label">Modules</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Modules tuned for high-risk, asset-intensive operations.</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
          Start with the intelligence layer, then activate the modules that matter most. AI4HSE can sit
          alongside your existing stack or gradually replace legacy tools.
        </p>

        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Incidents</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Multi-consequence incident intelligence</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Capture near misses, injuries, environmental events, process safety incidents, and regulatory
              reports — with AI-driven pattern detection across sites and contractors.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Field</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Inspections & audits</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Mobile-first inspections, QR-code assets, and audit programs that feed directly into the
              intelligence layer — no more dead checklists.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature">
            <div class="feature-label">Operations</div>
            <div class="feature-title">Permit to Work & LOTO</div>
            <p class="feature-body">
